Multimedia Lab offers the following services:        Lightboard Studio  Don't turn your back on your students! Our new lightboard studio is a twist on traditional lectures. Book a visit today!          Media Conversion  ACCC technology consultants will show you how to use the equipment and software to digitize or transcode your media.           Other Services     Closed Captioning   Faculty can request closed caption services for courses that are being converted to blended or online formats. Intro videos of 3-5 minutes are closed captioned at no cost to the faculty unit; longer videos require requestor’s departmental approval and payment.     Graphics   Faculty can request the creation of graphical elements to be used in their courses. Simple graphics are created at no cost to the faculty unit; more complex animations require requestor’s departmental approval and payment.     Equipment Lending   Both faculty and students can check out multimedia equipment for a short period of time; equipment includes laptops, camcorders, audio recorders, and more. The equipment is available at the Academic Multimedia Lab in the Daley Library IDEA Commons. ACCC technology consultants can show you how to use the equipment.     Multimedia Software Access   LTS technology consultants will show you how to use the equipment and software installed in the lab computers. The following software is available:   PC – Adobe Suite Creative Cloud (Full), Camtasia 9, Gimp2, VLC, Audacity, Handbrake, ImgBurn 2.5.7.0, Snagit  Mac – Adobe Suite Creative Cloud(Full), Camtasia 3, VLC, Handbrake, Snagit, Skitch      Video Production   Faculty can request recording and editing services for courses that are being converted to blended or online formats. Intro videos of 3-5 minutes are recorded and edited at no cost to the faculty unit; more in-depth videos require requestor’s departmental approval and payment.  As part of the video production service, ACCC technology consultants can meet with you to develop a storyboard for your videos.     Technical Assistance   ACCC technology consultants will help you with your audio, video, and eLearning Authoring software questions.  Multimedia consultations and technical assistance for your media projects are provided without a previous appointment and open to any student, faculty, and staff.          Google Maps image     Multimedia Lab  Open Monday - Friday, 9:00 am - 5:00 pm during academic semester. Walk-ins welcome!   801 South Morgan Street,  Richard Daley Library,  LIB 1-030,  Chicago,  Illinois  60607    Phone: (312)355-3385         Service Level Agreement       Service Request Fulfillment Time  Requests for service/information will be responded to within 1 business day. A specific timeline for completing the project will be given at the initial meeting/communication. Timeline is dependent upon the nature of the request and availability of resources. Projects are completed on a first-come, first-serve basis.    Incident Resolution Time  Within 2 business days (for problems with the media produced in the LTS multimedia lab)    Service Availability  9:00am - 5:00pm, Monday-Friday    Maintenance Window(s)  N/A    Service Notification Channel(s)  N/A    Reviewed to Ensure SLA Meets Business Requirements  Provisional SLA - Currently under IT Governance review    Date Reviewed  Provisional SLA - Currently under IT Governance review    Service Owner: Elizabeth Romero Fuerte               Services    Back to main content           Communication and Collaboration     Cloud Storage     Box    Google Drive    OneDrive      Conferencing     Blackboard Collaborate    Google Meet    Webex Meetings    Zoom      Digital Signage     Industry Weapon      Email and Calendaring     Exchange    Gmail    Google Calendar    Listserv      Emergency Communications     Startel    UIC Alert      Instant Messaging     Jabber      Phone Services     Automatic Call Distribution    Mobile Devices    Telephones    Voicemail      Productivity Software 